Sec. 2251.0031.  Exceptions for Certain Lines.   

(a)  Except as provided by Subsection (d), Subchapter C does not apply to any line of the 
following kinds of insurance written under a commercial insurance policy or contract issued by an 
insurer authorize d to engage in the business of insurance in this state:  
(1)  surety bonds;  
(2)  fidelity bonds;  
(3)  commercial inland marine;  
(4)  boiler and machinery;  
(5)  environmental impairment or pollution liability;  
(6)  kidnap and ransom;  
(7)  political risk or expropriation;  
(8)  commercial excess liability or umbrella liability;  
(9)  directors’ and officers’ liability;  
(10)  fiduciary liability;  
(11)  employment practices liability;  
(12)  errors and omission and professional liability other than medical profess ional liability;  
(13)  media liability;  
(14)  product liability, product recall, or completed operations;  
(15)  commercial cybersecurity, including first - and third -party commercial lines coverage for 
losses arising out of or relating to data privacy breac hes, network security, computer viruses, 
and similar exposures;  
(16)  highly protected commercial property;  
(17)  commercial flood insurance not provided through the National Flood Insurance Program; 
